From 7400908bd87835682f352942f40b826816efbc9b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 15:09:49 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 10 Batch 4 follow-up: kebab menu w/ "Mark as
 Automation"
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replace the inline text toggle with a 22px kebab button (vertical
ellipsis codicon) at the right edge of every comment header. Click
opens a context menu with a single action — "Mark as Automation" for
non-bots, "Mark as Discussion" for already-bots — that flips the
author's bot status for the active workspace.

The kebab is the right shape for adding more per-comment actions
later (resolve, copy permalink, …) without re-plumbing the chrome.
The button stays hidden until the comment is hovered (or the kebab
itself receives keyboard focus) so the timeline stays uncluttered.
---
 .../browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css   | 36 ++++-----
 .../browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.ts    | 74 ++++++++++---------
 2 files changed, 58 insertions(+), 52 deletions(-)

diff --git a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
index 0430efdf0b4..4a5ac163333 100644
--- a/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
+++ b/src/vs/workbench/contrib/krt/browser/pr/krtPullRequestEditorPane.css
@@ -442,37 +442,37 @@ img.krt-pr-comment-avatar {
 	flex: 1;
 }
 
-.krt-pr-comment-bot-toggle {
+.krt-pr-comment-menu-btn {
 	flex: 0 0 auto;
-	font: inherit;
-	font-size: 10.5px;
-	font-weight: 500;
+	width: 22px;
+	height: 22px;
+	display: inline-flex;
+	align-items: center;
+	justify-content: center;
 	color: var(--vscode-descriptionForeground);
